.TH PACSAT-DOWNLOAD 1 "December 27, 2025" "1.0.0" "PACSAT Revival Project"
.SH NAME
pacsat-download \- Download files from PACSAT ground station via REST API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B curl
\-OJ http://localhost:8000/download/\fIfile_num\fR
.br
\-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pacsat-download
is a command-line example for downloading files from the PACSAT ground station using the REST API.
Files are served with original PFH-derived filenames and support HTTP Range requests for resumable downloads.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-O
Save file with server-provided filename (Content-Disposition)
.TP
.B \-J
Use remote file name (combined with \-O)
.TP
.B \-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"
JWT authentication token obtained from /token endpoint
.TP
.B \-H "Range: bytes=start-end"
Request partial content for resumable download
.TP
.B /raw
Append /raw to URL for raw stored file (PFH + body) as .bin
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Download reconstructed file (original name)
    curl -OJ -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \\
         http://localhost:8000/download/1001
.TP
Download raw stored file
    curl -OJ -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \\
         http://localhost:8000/download/1001/raw
.TP
Partial/resumable download (first 1MB)
    curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \\
         -H "Range: bytes=0-1048575" \\
         -o partial.bin http://localhost:8000/download/1001
.SH RESPONSE
On success, returns file content with:
- Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="original_name.ext"
- Content-Length
- Accept-Ranges: bytes
- 206 Partial Content for Range requests
.SH AUTHENTICATION
First obtain token:
    curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/token" \\
         -d "username=youruser&password=yourpass"
